<br>
For all those rangers out there the attached website is fantastic for all Ranger quests, even, hushhhhhhh - Our Epic.<br>
<br>
Vlieke the Orc Impaler is noted here too as we briefly mentioned last night.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.monsterweb.org/faqs/q-rng-p.html#w-orc_impaler">www.monsterweb.org/faqs/q...rc_impaler</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Just take off the Orc impaler bit to get to the list - all the Ivy stuff is here, along with a total list of all items you need for all your quests, and where to get them.<br>
<br>
I've done that bracer quest - am Heading out to do Tunic after a brief spot of lvling at the weekend - that lvl 30 is beckoning.<br>
<br>
With the help of a friendly Pally you can take Redwind - the SK Orc in Everfrost pretty well, and he spawns every 7 minutes so no big waiting time. Drops the rune on average every other time. He /conned yellow to me at lvl 25, with 4 Icy Orc buddies who /conned white.<br>
<br>
Harmony all of them and Pull Redwind and his pet - pet is very green so dont worry about him. Get the pally to pull the guy with a bow, The SK will harm touch immediatley for 271 Hps, bah nothing to Mr lvl 31 Pally Araegorne, especially if he still has Loh. He is tough and a caster, get him snared or rooted so he cant go back to his pals and bach away. Get out your quick delay weapons 'cos interrupting his casting is real important. Let the Big Pally brute to the big damage.<br>
<br>
Once dead, finish his pet and heh presto.<br>
<br>
The Remaining Icy Orcs are good exp, but they take a while to kill, and when the new ones pop - if you havent Harmonied them you will be in a world of pain very quickly. <br>
<br>
The Tidal Lords in Dagnors cauldron have a spawn point at a camp past the fab 4 and head straight around the rocks till you find them. 2 at a time spawn fairly regularly. Harmony the 5/6 gobs that are there and pull the tidal to you and teach him the error of his ways.<br>
<br>
Anyhow - I am happy to help all who quest, finding it a great diversion from the sometimes annoying lvling drive. <br>
<br>
Vlieke - happy to come along and provide moral support if you wanna go get the Impaler, or ohh - Epic time soon huh?? <p>Semdayen Maa'Sankari<Br>Ranger of the 26th Season<Br>In the Service of Tunare<Br><Br>'I am not lost - this is the scenic route'
